Origin of sfx / samples used in blobwars
----------------------------------------

Note all samples have been made mono

From other games:
-----------------

From bzflag, LGPLv2.1:
pop1.wav          bzflag/pop.wav

From freedoom, BSD:
weaponPickup.wav  freedoom/sounds/dswpnup.wav
death1.wav        freedoom/sounds/dspodth1.wav
death2.wav        freedoom/sounds/dspodth2.wav
death3.wav        freedoom/sounds/dspodth3.wav
galdovSplit.wav   freedoom/sounds/dstelept.wav

From nexuiz, GPLv2:
machinegun.wav    nexuiz-20091001/sound/weapons/uzi_fire.ogg
                  (begin copy pasted 3x, end removed)
plasma.wav        nexuiz-20091001/sound/weapons/hook_fire.ogg
                  (silence at the end removed)
rocket.wav        nexuiz-20091001/sound/weapons/rocket_fire.ogg
                  (slightly (15%) sped up)
teleport1.wav     nexuiz-20091001/sound/misc/teleport.ogg

From openarena, GPLv2:
menu.wav          baseoa/sound/misc/menu1.wav
select.wav        baseoa/sound/items/m_health.wav
pistol.wav        baseoa/sound/weapons/machinegun/machgf1b.wav
                  (made 1.0 db louder with clipping in audacity)
switch.wav        baseoa/sound/movers/switches/butn2.wav

From openquartz, GPLv2:
rico2.wav         pak0/sound/weapons/ric2.wav
